The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Castrol India reports flat growth

 New Delhi, July 22 (PTI): Castrol India has reported a profit after tax of Rs 50 crore in the second quarter ended June 30 against Rs 49 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal, registering a flat growth of 2 per cent.

 The company board has recommended a dividend of Rs 4 per share for the half-year ended June 30.

 Net sales during the quarter rose 21 per cent to Rs 477 crore from Rs 395 crore in the year-ago period.

 The company said while the topline outlook for the rest of the year will be positive, the profit scenario will continue to be challenging given the risk of further escalation in input costs on the back of rising crude oil prices. 

 M amp;M Financial

 Driven by the twin factors of volume growth and increase in lending rates, Mahindra amp; Mahindra Financial Services Ltd (MMFSL) has registered a 45 per cent rise in its revenue at Rs 165 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal compared with Rs 114 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

 The company, a part of the Mahindra group, has clocked a 13 per cent increase in its profit after tax at Rs 19.23 crore against Rs 16.99 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

 Mahindra amp; Mahindra Financial has also increased its branch network from 305 to 356 at the end of the quarter.

 Its wholly-owned subsidiary, Mahindra Insurance Brokers Ltd (MIBL), which is into the business of direct insurance broking, has also reported a 124 per cent rise in its income in the quarter at Rs 2.66 crore against Rs 1.19-crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.

 Profit before tax jumped 63 per cent to Rs 1.5 crore from Rs 0.92-crore. 

 Bajaj Hindustan

 Sugar and ethanol company Bajaj Hindustan Ltd (BHL) today posted an increase of 21 per cent in its net profit for the third quarter at Rs 63.9 crore against Rs 53 crore in the corresponding quarter previous year.

 Total income during the quarter rose 22 per cent to Rs 449.2 crore compared with Rs 366.9 crore for the same period a year ago, the company informed the National Stock Exchange.

 Earnings before interest, depreciation, taxes and amortisation during the third quarter rose 31 per cent to Rs 110.6 crore from Rs 84.3 crore in the year-ago period. 




